## Data Structures

### `Task` Class

Represents a single task.

**Main attributes:** - `int id` - `std::string title` -
`std::string description` - `Status status` - `Priority priority` -
`std::string dueDate`

**Enums used:**

``` cpp
enum class Status { PENDING, IN_PROGRESS, DONE };
enum class Priority { LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH };
```

---

### `TaskManager` Class

Responsible for managing all tasks.

**Main responsibilities:** - Add tasks - Remove tasks by ID - Update
task - List tasks

**Internal structure:**

``` cpp
std::vector<Task> tasks;
```

---

## Data Persistence

Tasks are stored in a text file using the following format:

``` text
id|title|description|status|priority|dueDate
```

The file is automatically loaded when the program starts.

